ONBOARD_TITLE_6: Ready to Unleash Your Creativity with Rodin
ONBOARD_CONTENT_1_1: Rodin is utilizing a native 3D large generative model with over ~1.5 billion parameters~ aims to create production-ready 3D assets.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_1_2: To better understand Rodin's strengths and weaknesses, we would like to first share the ~design principles~ behind it.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_2_1: Rodin aims to create ~production-ready~ 3D assets, so we place significant emphasis on the **structures**, **wireframe**, and **PBR textures**.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_2_2: As a ~3D Native Diffusion Transformer~, Rodin was trained on pure 3D meshes, preserved high-level geometric features such as ~sharp edges and hard surfaces~.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_3_1: Unlike previous 3D GenAI tools that resemble a Large Reconstruction Models, Rodin Gen-1 functions more like a ~language model~.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_3_2: Rodin aims to ~understand and remodel~ image features into 3D outputs, which is more  solid and diversity though some details may ~differ~ from inputs.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_3_3: If similarity of input view is your priority over Production-Ready, there are better options available.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_4_1: Rodin aims to create a 3D GenAI that can ~collaborate with humans~.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_4_2: ~Redo~ is the core feature of Rodin. During the generation process, users can influence the output by ~adjusting the prompt~ and applying new prompts through ~Redo~. Alternatively, users can simply use ~Redo~ to generate with another random seed.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_4_3: If you're looking for a one-click, purely AI-driven solution, better options are available.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_5_1: Over the past year, the field of 3D generation has seen a surge of excellent products.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_5_2: Rodin Gen-1 offers a more unique option.
ONBOARD_CONTENT_5_3: AI is just a ~tool~. 3D GenAI is still ~immature~. We are grateful to the 3D community for welcoming us. In the future, Rodin will introduce ~more features~ to the platform.
